        private Message dequeue​(java.util.concurrent.BlockingQueue<Message> messages,
                        int timeout,
                        java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit unit)
                 throws java.lang.InterruptedException,
                        java.util.concurrent.TimeoutException
        Given a queue, this method returns the first pending message, waiting if necessary for the specified timeout
        Parameters:
        messages - the queue to listen for new messages
        timeout - the maximum timeout
        unit - the measurement unit of the timeout
        Returns:
        the first message removed from the queue
        Throws:
        java.lang.InterruptedException - if the thread is forced to stop
        java.util.concurrent.TimeoutException - if the timeout has been reached without receiving any message
